HEADWORD: Cogency
<hw>Co"gen*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Cogent</er>.]</ety> <def>The quality of being cogent; power of
compelling conviction; conclusiveness; force.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An antecedent argument of extreme <qex>cogency</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>J. H. Newman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cogenial</ent>⟦br⟧
